TA-25 Index gains 0.9% at 4:30 pm
close in Tel Aviv.  ADVANCERS
*  Avgol (AVGL)   +2.2%; Israel Petrochemical says in talks with
foreign investment fund to sell stake in co.
*  EZchip (EZCH)   +7%
*  Babylon (BBYL)   +5%; Calcalist says Co. seeking to raise $1b
via Nasdaq listing; co. official declines to comment
*  Israel Chemicals (ICL)   +4.3%; heat waves in Southern Europe
and U.S. drought are withering corn crops
*  Shemen (SMOG)   +23%, gains 42% in two days after co. yday
said accord signed with Israel Defense Ministry to allow
drilling in the Yam 3 field
*  Silicom (SILC)   + 7.2%; U.S. shrs rose 6.7% yday as 2Q rev.
advanced 11% and net income increased 16% yoy  DECLINERS
*  Bank Leumi (LUMI)   -2.2 %;  Bank Hapoalim (POLI)   -2%;  Bank
Discount (DSCT)   -0.4%; Citigroup sees outlook for Israeli
